    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-01-24T20:26:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-01-24T20:26:00-05:00" n="462"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d462">
                <head>462. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Thailand</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d462fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 792.00/1–2458. Secret. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_BRH1"
                            >Bushner</persName> and <persName>Walter G. Stoneman</persName> of
                            <gloss target="#t_ICA1">ICA</gloss>, cleared with the Department of
                        Defense, and approved by Gardner Palmer.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1958-01-24T20:26:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 24, 1958—8:26 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1931. Joint State–<gloss target="#t_ICA1">ICA</gloss>–Defense. Department’s
                        1102.<note n="2" xml:id="d462fn2">In telegram 1102, October 24, 1957, State,
                            <gloss target="#t_ICA1">ICA</gloss>, and Defense expressed concurrence
                        in the aid program approach proposed in telegram 1056 from Bangkok October
                        5, 1957, which is printed in <ref target="frus1955-57v22#pg_938">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1955–1957, vol. XXII, p.
                            938</ref>.</note> Despite inclusion in Thai Cabinet several ministers
                    whose foreign policy views are questionable, appears from official position
                    taken by Government leaders (example Government policy statement and <persName
                        corresp="#p_KLGT1">Thanom</persName> New Year address), as well as Embassy
                    analysis (Embtel 1896)<note n="3" xml:id="d462fn3">See <ref target="#d458fn3"
                            >footnote 3, Document 458</ref>.</note> that Government is maintaining
                    favorable posture re collective security, Communism and Free World. Therefore
                    unless you see objection we are prepared proceed with normal programming and
                    obligational process for current fiscal year.<note n="4" xml:id="d462fn4">In
                        telegram 2190 from Bangkok, January 28, the Country Team concurred.
                        (Department of State, Central Files, 792.00/1–2858)</note>
                </p>
                <p>For <gloss target="#t_USOM1">USOM</gloss>: Have received and are processing FY 58
                    operational program (<gloss target="#t_Toica1">Toica</gloss> A–989).<note n="5"
                        xml:id="d462fn5">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HCA1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Herter</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
